1
00:00:02,080 --> 00:00:03,877
-Previously on The O. C. :
-Rebecca is gone.

2
00:00:04,080 --> 00:00:06,594
-What did you say to her?
-I asked her if she was in love with you.

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,074
And she said she was.

4
00:00:08,280 --> 00:00:11,431
-I tried to tell Summer, and I couldn't.
-So you' re here to break up with me?

5
00:00:11,640 --> 00:00:14,837
-Then I told her.
-I believe in taking every precaution.

6
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:17,713
-Caleb's gonna ask for a DNA test.
-You can't let him adopt you.

7
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:20,195
-What are you talking about?
-He might not be your dad.

8
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:22,078
When we were about to...

9
00:00:22,280 --> 00:00:24,191
-...there was this voice in my head.
-Seth?

10
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,595
Have a great time in ltaly.
I'm cool with it.

11
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:29,270
I'm over you.

12
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:39,871
Well, I cannot believe I'm saying this,
but it's raining in the O. C.

13
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:41,877
I know, it's crazy.
I gotta tell you...

14
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:44,076
... traffic is a nightmare.
The 405 is jammed.

15
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:46,196
The 5, the 7 10, they 're all gridlocked.

16
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:49,318
Stay safe, stay dry,
and let 's all pray for sunshine again.

17
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:58,558
Hey, I kind of need to talk to you...

18
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:02,599
-...so you coming over for breakfast?
-Need to clean. Swing by the pool house.

19
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,751
Look out the window.
It's the sequence...

20
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,956
-...from Day After Tomorrow.
-It's just rain.

21
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:09,395
-I'll be here if you need to talk.
-Dude, come on.

22
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:13,036
I'm a child of Southern California.
I can't go out in this. I'll melt.

23
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:17,189
-You wanna do it over the phone?
-Works for me.

24
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,911
So does this weather.

25
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:23,993
It's very reflective
of my current emotional state.

26
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:26,316
Yeah, I know what you mean.

27
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:30,789
So I'm gonna lose her, man.

28
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:33,520
Summer's leaving for ltaly tomorrow.
It'll be nothing...

29
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,716
...but cannolis and canoodling
with Zach.

30
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,394
Haven't talked to Lindsay
since she ran out of Caleb's.

31
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:41,711
-You should talk to her.
-She won't talk to anyone.

32
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:44,394
I don't know. Maybe it'll
all work out for the best.

33
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,192
Yeah, maybe.

34
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:52,312
You don't think that's God trying
to tell us anything, do you?

35
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:55,040
Not gonna take that chance.
I've gotta talk to Lindsay.

36
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,872
You think we should stick together?

37
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,917
Kind of two by two, like Noah did.

38
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:01,275
He's very wise, Ryan. He had a beard.

39
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:03,550
It's just rain. It can't hurt us.

40
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,395
Not worse than our women can.

41
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:09,710
It's 1 0:00.

42
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,789
Are you gonna stay in bed all day?

43
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:14,552
Maybe.

44
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:16,756
I like it here.

45
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:23,992
Oh, I feel like-- Like we've
become like strangers.

46
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:27,197
Well, I was taught never
to talk to strangers.

47
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:28,994
Funny.

48
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:31,151
Not trying to be.

49
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,156
-Well, I'm sorry you're upset.
-Really?

50
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,999
Because the last time I checked,
everything was my fault.

51
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:40,549
-I never said that.
-Not in those exact words.

52
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,198
-Hello.
-Sandy.

53
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:58,275
-Rebecca.
-Now I'm up.

54
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:00,357
I wanted to run, Sandy. I...

55
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:02,909
...got on a bus. I was on my way.

56
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:05,992
But I realized I couldn't leave
without saying goodbye.

57
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:07,559
As long as you don't flee...

58
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:12,117
...we have a chance with your case.
Please, stay where you are.

59
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:26,235
-Hey.
-Good morning, Marissa.

60
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,753
Oh, I didn't know you
had a friend over last night.

61
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,518
-I'm Julie Cooper-Nichol.
-Alex.

62
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:34,359
Oh, so you're the feisty young lady
Caleb mentioned.

63
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:37,557
I was just making bagels.
If the Cohens can do it, why can't we?

64
00:05:37,760 --> 00:05:40,069
None for me, thanks.
I don't eat breakfast.

65
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:43,198
That's very punk of you.
I used to like the punk in my day.

66
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,755
-Mom.
-You're right, Marissa. It still is my day.

67
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,911
I was just being modest.

68
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:52,797
We'll be keeping kosher in no time.

69
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:57,312
So how about this weather, huh?

70
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:00,354
-It's unbelievable.
-Yeah.

71
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,915
I think I have to go.
But very nice to meet you.

72
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,231
Rock on.

73
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,513
She seems nice.

74
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:11,076
No problem if you want
a friend to stay over.

75
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:14,232
-lf you could let me know beforehand--
-You didn't get the memo?

76
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:17,917
Marissa, I don't think it's too much
to ask to know what's going on...

77
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:20,116
...underneath my roof. That's all.

78
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:23,670
You want to know what's going on
with me? I'm gonna tell you the truth.

79
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:26,348
No screaming. No crying.
Just the truth.

80
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:29,028
You have no idea how happy
it makes me to hear that.

81
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,959
Hold that thought.
Alex is my girlfriend.

82
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:34,230
I know. I'm happy that
you've made a friend.

83
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:36,590
-Though I hope we keep seeing Summer.
-No, Mom.

84
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,910
Not my friend who's a girl.

85
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:41,036
My girlfriend.

86
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:45,471
Yeah.

87
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:27,350
-What are you doing?
-You wouldn't open the door.

88
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:30,114
-Because I don't want to see anyone.
-Please let me in.

89
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:32,874
I rode my bike here.
Bicycle, monsoon...

90
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:35,389
...seriously flawed plan. I'm freezing.

91
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,639
Come on.

92
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,639
-Are you okay?
-Yeah, no.

93
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,518
All right. Hold on.

94
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:50,475
Okay. Come here.

95
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,359
Well, you could've opened the door
for me a half-hour ago.

96
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:05,838
I thought you were Caleb, showing up
to drive me to my DNA test.

97
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:09,353
He scheduled you a DNA test?

98
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,831
It was either that or the pony.

99
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:15,476
-So you're not going?
-No way.

100
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:20,275
But you're going somewhere.

101
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:23,119
Yeah, I was gonna pack up
to move in with my dad.

102
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:25,350
But since he might not be my dad...

103
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:28,798
...I was thinking
about packing up for...

104
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:31,030
...well, maybe...

105
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:34,109
...I don't know, Chicago.

106
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,714
"l don't know, Chicago"?

107
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:42,909
Yeah. We have family there.

108
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:45,276
Actual, no-doubt-about-it family.

109
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:50,156
And my mom is thinking that
it getting out about her and Caleb...

110
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:53,392
...that maybe the best thing
would be...

111
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,039
...to start over.

112
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,395
And you'd go with her.

113
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,918
Well, if Caleb's not my dad,
what else can I do?

114
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,910
Except you don't know
he's not your dad.

115
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:11,755
I don't know that I want to know.

116
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:14,110
That's not gonna stop
until you know the truth.

117
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:18,069
And besides, if you are his daughter...

118
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,196
...at least you'll have a reason to stay.

119
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:25,312
I mean, the other reason.

120
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,638
I don't know, Ryan.

121
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:38,112
A DNA test just sounds so sci-fi scary.

122
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,679
I'll go with you.

123
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,394
Okay.

124
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,753
Who looks good in this much yellow?

125
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:54,833
Zach?

126
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:58,754
Oh, thank God. Look, I really
don't know about this dress.

127
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:01,673
Hi. It's just your friendly
neighborhood Seth Cohen.

128
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:06,399
-Okay. What?
-Well, I look stupid in hats.

129
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,630
And I don't have a raincoat...

130
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:11,917
...so Spider-Man is the only
protective waterproof headgear I own.

131
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,395
T oo bad you weren't wearing
protective headgear...

132
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:16,790
...when you were dropped
on your head as a child.

133
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:21,078
Zing. So listen...

134
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:25,279
...I know that my visits to your bedroom
are probably getting a little bit repetitive.

135
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:28,154
-You are helping me miss you less.
-That's great.

136
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:30,151
So....

137
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:34,633
-You're really going, huh?
-Yeah. Of course I'm going.

138
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:37,519
How could I not be?
I am in his sister's wedding.

139
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,954
-You are?
-Why do you think...

140
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:42,317
...I look like lemon meringue?
Bridesmaid's dress.

141
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,471
You're a bridesmaid?

142
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,271
That's really....

143
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:52,871
-Guess you and Zach are serious.
-Cohen, are we gonna do this again?

144
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:55,713
Or did you, like, actually come here
to advance the plot.

145
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:58,314
You're, like, part of his family.

146
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:02,393
Okay.

147
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:05,632
The reason I came by is to tell you...

148
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:09,312
...you need to take a special plug
for the outlets there.

149
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:12,677
For your hair dryer. Don't want you
to brownout Western Europe.

150
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:17,390
Goodbye, again.
And you have a safe flight.

151
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:59,157
-Thanks for coming.
-Oh, it wasn't easy.

152
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:02,557
It rains in Southern California,
all of a sudden, nobody can drive.

153
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,911
You're shaking.

154
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:12,234
I don't wanna run anymore.

155
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:15,472
-Come back with me.
-And do what? Sit in jail?

156
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:16,999
Destroy your marriage?

157
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,788
My marriage has
nothing to do with your case.

158
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,197
Come back with me. We'll explore
amnesty or some kind of plea bargain.

159
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,992
I think we can make this right.

160
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:40,551
-I told her.
-You told who what?

161
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:44,076
My mom, about us.
I can't believe it, but I did.

162
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:47,073
You-- You told her.

163
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:49,193
Well, I thought you'd be happy.

164
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,437
No, l-- It just depends.
Did you tell her to piss her off?

165
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:56,434
Hey, look. I told her
so this could be real.

166
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,877
For us.

167
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:04,632
So, what happens now?

168
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:07,479
She's probably having
a meltdown. I can't go home.

169
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:09,272
-So stay here.
-You sure?

170
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:11,311
Yeah.

171
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:15,791
But first, let's get you
out of these wet clothes.

172
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,230
Thanks for coming with me.

173
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:34,675
What's more romantic
than a DNA test?

174
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:38,913
Yeah. Maybe we can donate
kidneys one Saturday night.

175
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:41,156
Now we're talking.

176
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:51,235
So if, in 24 hours,
it turns out Caleb is my dad....

177
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:55,790
You talking dirty to me?

178
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,313
Sorry.

179
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:02,473
Well, if the tests come back positive,
then he'll adopt you, right?

180
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,473
Right.

181
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:10,035
Except, I don't know
if I want him to adopt me.

182
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,430
Well, you're not going to Chicago.

183
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:14,318
Let's just forget about that option.

184
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,638
No, l--

185
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:18,833
I know that.

186
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,275
I couldn't handle the cold...

187
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:23,317
-...and the wind.
-lt is the Windy City.

188
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:25,198
I'm not a big fan of deep-dish pizza.

189
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:27,555
Thin crust, only way to go.

190
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:31,635
And I couldn't be without you.

191
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:39,799
So I come in right below pizza.
That's good to know.

192
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:43,430
Yeah, well, a girl's gotta eat.

193
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:55,071
What are you doing here
late on a Saturday?

194
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:59,995
Oh, hey, Julie. I'm just trying
to distract myself and failing.

195
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:02,276
-What about you?
-Same.

196
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,476
How long is this weather
supposed to last?

197
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:05,993
News says 24 hours.

198
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:09,357
-I don't think my hair can take it.
-I don't know if my marriage can.

199
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:12,279
Gossip?

200
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,839
You have no idea.

201
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:17,317
Want to break into
Caleb's liquor cabinet, dish some dirt?

202
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:26,791
-I'd like to use this on Caleb sometimes.
-I know what you mean.

203
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,592
-More Scotch?
-Sure, why not?

204
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:32,349
Nothing like a rainy day to reflect
on what a mess your life is, huh?

205
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:37,111
I mean, not yours, per se.
It was, you know, the universal "you. "

206
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:41,393
My life is a pretty big mess.
I may even beat you on that one.

207
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,750
Oh, I don't think so, honey,
but go ahead.

208
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:48,436
Well, my husband is currently
transporting a fugitive...

209
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,114
...who used to be his ex-girlfriend.

210
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:55,034
Well, I'll see your fugitive former flame
and raise you a lesbian daughter.

211
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,798
Marissa?

212
00:15:57,920 --> 00:16:00,229
Well, I'm sure it's just a phase.

213
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,436
It was for me.

214
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:07,072
And it is for you too.
You guys will work it out.

215
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:11,877
-I'm not so sure.
-No...

216
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:14,156
...Kirsten, seriously,
you have to work it out.

217
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:19,678
I couldn't handle it if you didn't. You
two are the moral center of the universe.

218
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:21,999
You're Sandy and Kirsten.

219
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:28,150
Yeah, well, now we're
Sandy and Kirsten and Rebecca.

220
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:38,515
-Oh, no, police.
-Take it easy. We're fine.

221
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:44,392
The road's
completely washed out ahead.

222
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:47,677
We need you to turn around. We should
have the road open by morning.

223
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,671
-Not till morning?
-Yes, sir.

224
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:52,229
There's lodging a few miles back.

225
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:55,198
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

226
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:10,788
You're listening to Boyz ll Men?

227
00:17:11,320 --> 00:17:14,630
I can think of no sadder song
in the whole world.

228
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:17,155
So I'm guessing it didn't go well.

229
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:26,149
Unless I can think of one last grand
romantic gesture, Summer's gone.

230
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:30,230
I remember when I first heard
about Summer.

231
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:33,119
We were sailing. You said
you named your boat after her...

232
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:35,555
...which I thought weird.
You'd never talked to her.

233
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:39,235
Eureka, Ryan. Can't believe I just
said "eureka. " That's okay. That's it.

234
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,032
-What's it?
-Thing to win her back.

235
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:44,954
The grand romantic gesture that's
gonna put Zachary's Euro-trip to shame.

236
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:49,557
I shall take her on a sailing adventure
aboard the Summer Breeze.

237
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:55,192
-Except you sold the boat for bus fare.
-I did. Damn it.

238
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:58,995
Eureka, Ryan. I shall buy back
